<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-641-278  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 641 278.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  July 16 1990 v7 n29 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Ex-Lotus exec Kapor forms users rights organization. (MitchellKapor, late of Lotus Development Corp., forms The ElectronicFrontier Foundation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Messmer, Ellen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Mitchell Kapor, president of ON Technology Inc, and Steven Jobs ofNext Inc have established the Electronic Frontier Foundation topreserve the civil liberties of computer users.andP;  Kapor blamespublic ignorance for what he maintains are breaches of the FirstAmendment by law enforcement agencies.andP;  The foundation, accordingto Kapor, will offer education about social issues in computercommunication.andP;  The foundation is paying the legal expenses ofSteve Jackson, whose equipment was confiscated because the SecretService felt a handbook he published promoted computer crime.andO;According to a foundation associate, the Electronic FrontierFoundation is not a 'hacker defense fund.' Another issue it'slooking into concerns the liability of electronic bulletin boardowners for on-line messages.andP;  According to Kapor, theorganization's main goal is to ensure digital media is subject tothe same rights as other media.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   ON Technology Inc. (officials and employees).andO;Topic:     Electronic Frontier FoundationUser NeedsUser RelationsLegal IssuesLaw EnforcementSocial IssuesFoundations.andO;Person:    Jobs, Steven (social policy); Kapor, Mitchell (social policy).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>